// ----------------------------------------------------------------
// Traits by type
// ----------------------------------------------------------------

Table: trait_Undead
Undead Fortitude: If damage reduces this creature to 0 HP, it must make a CON save (DC {1d4 + 8}) or drop to 1 HP instead.
Turn Resistance: Advantage on saving throws against effects that turn undead.
Sunlight Sensitivity: Disadvantage on attack rolls and Perception checks in sunlight.
Incorporeal Movement: Can move through creatures and objects as difficult terrain.
Necrotic Aura: Creatures within 10 ft take {1d4} necrotic damage at the start of their turn.
Rejuvenation: If destroyed, re-forms in {1d10} days unless its phylactery is also destroyed.
Death's Boon: When a creature within 30 ft dies, this creature regains {1d8 + 4} HP.
Ethereal Sight: Can see into the Ethereal Plane out to 60 ft.
Haunting Presence: Creatures within 60 ft have disadvantage on death saving throws.
Spectral Form: On its turn, can become incorporeal until the start of its next turn (AC becomes 13, immune to non-magical weapons).
Life Leech Aura: At the start of each of its turns, one creature it can see within 30 ft loses {1d6} HP (no save); the creature regains that much HP.

Table: trait_Beast
Keen Smell: Advantage on Perception checks relying on smell.
Pack Tactics: Advantage on attack rolls when an ally is adjacent to the target.
Charge: If it moves 20 ft toward a target and hits, the target must make a STR save (DC {1d4 + 10}) or be knocked prone.
Spider Climb: Can climb difficult surfaces without ability checks.
Swarm: Can occupy another creature's space; reduces to 0 HP by fire damage.
Pounce: After a charge, it can use a bonus action to make a bite attack.
Blood Frenzy: Advantage on melee attack rolls against any creature that doesn't have all its HP.
Echolocation: Cannot use blindsight while deafened.
Relentless (Recharge after Short/Long Rest): If it takes 20 or fewer damage that would reduce it to 0 HP, it is reduced to 1 HP instead.
Water Breathing: Can breathe only underwater. Speed 0 on land; swim speed 40 ft.
Keen Hearing and Smell: Advantage on Perception checks that rely on hearing or smell.
Camouflage: Has advantage on DEX (Stealth) checks when in [|forest|rocky|aquatic|desert|underground] terrain.
Web Walker: Ignores movement restrictions caused by webbing; can detect vibrations in web up to 60 ft away.

Table: trait_Humanoid
Martial Advantage: Deals an extra {2d6} damage once per turn if an ally is adjacent to the target.
Tactical Retreat: Can Disengage as a bonus action.
Battle Cry: Allies within 30 ft gain advantage on their next attack (1/day).
Shield Wall: +2 AC when adjacent to another humanoid with a shield.
Veteran's Instinct: Cannot be surprised.
Spellcasting: Knows {1d3 + 1} spells of level {1d3}.
Skirmisher: Can move up to half its speed as a reaction when a creature ends its turn adjacent to it.
Net Tactics: Once per turn, when it hits with a melee attack, it can attempt to grapple the target as a bonus action.
Bloodied Fury: When reduced below half HP, gains advantage on all attack rolls until end of its next turn.
Coordinated Assault: When it hits a creature that another humanoid has also attacked this round, deals an extra {1d8} damage.
Indomitable (1/day): Can reroll a saving throw it fails, keeping the new result.

Table: trait_Fiend
Magic Resistance: Advantage on saving throws against spells and magical effects.
Fire Immunity: Immune to fire damage.
Telepathy: Communicates telepathically with any creature within 120 ft.
Aura of Fear: Creatures within 20 ft must succeed on a WIS save (DC {1d4 + 12}) or be frightened.
Devil's Sight: Sees through darkness, magical or otherwise, up to 120 ft.
Shapeshifter: Can take the form of any humanoid as an action.
Corrupting Touch: Creatures struck by its melee attacks must make CON saves (DC {1d4 + 13}) or gain 1 level of exhaustion.
Soul Hunger: When a humanoid within 60 ft dies, the fiend regains {2d10} HP.
Planar Step (3/day): Teleports itself and up to 2 willing creatures to any location in the same plane.
Infernal Gaze: Can target one creature within 30 ft; target makes WIS save (DC {1d4 + 14}) or is frightened and stunned until the end of its next turn.
Aura of Corruption: Non-fiend creatures within 20 ft have disadvantage on saving throws against spells and magical effects.

Table: trait_Dragon
Legendary Resistance (3/day): Can choose to succeed on a failed saving throw.
Frightful Presence: Creatures within 120 ft must make a WIS save or be frightened for 1 minute.
Magic Resistance: Advantage on saving throws against spells.
Blindsight 60 ft: Perceives its environment without relying on sight.
Amphibious: Can breathe air and water.
Multiattack: Makes {1d2 + 1} attacks per action.
Wing Buffet: Each creature within 15 ft when the dragon takes off must make a DEX save (DC {1d4 + 16}) or be knocked prone.
Draconic Majesty: While not incapacitated, the dragon projects an aura of dominance — creatures with CR or level less than the dragon's have disadvantage on ability checks against it.
Tail Reaction: On being missed by a melee attack, the dragon can make a tail attack as a reaction.
Lair Actions: On initiative count 20 (losing ties), takes one lair action (wall of fire/fog/rockfall — chosen at encounter start).
Flyby: Doesn't provoke opportunity attacks when it flies out of an enemy's reach.

Table: trait_Construct
Immutable Form: Immune to any spell or effect that alters its form.
Magic Resistance: Advantage on saving throws against spells.
Magic Weapons: Its attacks count as magical.
Antimagic Susceptibility: Incapacitated in an antimagic field.
Self-Repairing: Regains {1d6} HP at the start of its turn if it has at least 1 HP.
Powerful Build: Counts as one size larger for grappling and carrying.
Creator's Loyalty: Won't harm a creature it recognises as its creator or designated ally unless magically compelled.
Berserk Threshold: If reduced below {1d4 * 10} HP, rolls d6 at turn start; on 1–3, attacks the nearest creature regardless of allegiance.
Siege Engine: When deployed against a fortification, deals {2d10} extra damage per turn to structures.
Unstoppable: Is not slowed by difficult terrain.
Reactive Plating: As a reaction, can increase its AC by 5 until the start of its next turn (1/round).

Table: trait_Aberration
Alien Mind: Immune to the charmed and frightened conditions.
Telepathic Bond: Linked to up to {1d4} creatures it has charmed.
Amorphous: Can move through spaces as narrow as 1 inch without squeezing.
Psychic Sight: Senses thoughts within 30 ft.
Reality Warp: Once per turn, teleports up to 30 ft as a bonus action.
Mind Blast Recharge (5–6): Emits a psychic wave in a 60 ft cone.
Gibbering: Each creature that starts its turn within 20 ft must make a WIS save (DC {1d4 + 12}) or be unable to take reactions until the start of its next turn.
Eldritch Leech: When it damages a creature with a spell or psychic attack, it regains HP equal to half the damage dealt.
Phase Step: Can enter and exit the Ethereal Plane as a bonus action.
Spatial Distortion: The area within 30 ft of it is subtly warped — creatures that try to move away must succeed on a WIS save (DC {1d4 + 11}) or waste their movement.
Composite Biology: Has {1d4 + 1} separate vital organs — must be reduced to 0 HP {1d2 + 1} times before truly dying.

Table: trait_Fey
Fey Step: Can teleport up to 30 ft to a visible location as a bonus action.
Magic Resistance: Advantage on saving throws against spells.
Innate Spellcasting: Casts [|charm person|invisibility|misty step|entangle|sleep|faerie fire|plant growth] at will.
Evasion: Takes no damage on successful DEX saves, half on failed ones.
Glamour: Can create illusory disguises as an action.
Nature's Ward: Immune to poison and the poisoned condition.
Bewildering Dance: Creatures within 30 ft that watch the creature move must make WIS saves (DC {1d4 + 12}) or waste their movement walking toward the fey.
Thorned Hide: When a creature deals melee damage to this creature, the attacker takes {1d4} piercing damage.
Lure of the Wild: Beasts and plants within 60 ft are charmed by the fey (no save) as long as it doesn't harm them.
Mistshroud: If it starts its turn in dim light or darkness, it becomes invisible until it attacks or moves into bright light.
Vengeful Glamour: When charmed by the fey, creatures believe any attack made against them was made by the creature they trust most.

Table: trait_Giant
Powerful Build: Counts as Huge for carrying capacity and grappling.
Rock Catching: If a rock or similar projectile is thrown at it, it can catch it (DC {1d4 + 10} DEX save).
Siege Monster: Deals double damage to objects and structures.
Thunderous Stomp: Movement triggers a DC {1d4 + 12} STR save for adjacent creatures or they fall prone.
Reckless Attack: Has advantage on all attack rolls this turn; attackers also have advantage against it.
Multiattack: Makes 2 melee attacks per action.
Regeneration: Regains {1d10 + 5} HP at the start of its turn unless it took fire or acid damage in the previous round.
Fear Aura: Creatures of Medium size or smaller within 30 ft must make WIS saves (DC {1d4 + 12}) at the start of their turns or be frightened.
Sweeping Strike: When it hits one creature with a melee attack, it can extend the strike to a second adjacent creature (same attack roll vs both).
Boulder Lunge: If it begins its turn prone, it can stand up and immediately throw a boulder as part of the same action.
Ancient Memory: Advantage on History checks. Knows the location of all major settlements within 100 miles of its current position.

Table: trait_Ooze
Amorphous: Can squeeze through 1-inch gaps without difficulty.
Corrosive Form: Creatures that touch it or hit with melee attacks take {1d4} acid damage.
Engulf: Can engulf a restrained creature on its turn.
False Appearance: While motionless, indistinguishable from a puddle of liquid.
Split: When subjected to lightning or slashing, splits into two smaller oozes.
Transparent: Has disadvantage on Stealth checks only in brightly lit areas.
Ooze Cube: Fills its entire space; creatures must make DEX saves (DC {1d4 + 12}) or be engulfed on contact.
Acid Trail: Leaves a trail of acid wherever it moves; the trail is difficult terrain and deals {1d6} acid damage per turn to creatures within it.
Mindless: Immune to all conditions that affect the mind (charm, fear, psychic damage, etc.).
Pseudopod Grapple: Each successful pseudopod attack grapples its target (escape DC {1d4 + 12}). It can grapple up to {1d2 + 1} creatures simultaneously.
Nutrient Absorption: When it fully digests a creature (reduces it to 0 HP while engulfed), it increases maximum HP by {1d8 + 4} permanently.

Table: trait_Plant
False Appearance: While motionless among vegetation, indistinguishable from a normal plant.
Regeneration: Regains {1d8 + 3} HP at the start of its turn unless it took fire damage in the previous round.
Spider Climb: Can move across ceilings and walls without ability checks (vine-based movement).
Spore Cloud: Creatures within 15 ft at the start of their turns must make CON saves (DC {1d4 + 11}) or be poisoned for 1 minute.
Root Network: Can communicate with other plants within 120 ft; can sense movement through the root network.
Photosynthesis: In bright light, regenerates {1d6} HP per turn. In darkness, loses {1d4} HP per turn.
Thorns: A creature that grapples or is grappled by the plant takes {1d4} piercing damage per turn.
Vine Trap: The plant's area counts as difficult terrain; creatures must make STR saves (DC {1d4 + 12}) or be restrained on entering.
Blight Aura: Nonmagical plants within 30 ft wilt and die. Ground within 30 ft is blighted difficult terrain.

Table: trait_Monstrosity
Multiattack: Makes {1d2 + 1} attacks per action, using different natural weapons.
Trampling Charge: Knocks targets prone (DC {1d4 + 13} STR save) when it charges 20 ft and hits.
Petrifying Gaze: Targets that start their turn within 30 ft must make CON saves (DC {1d4 + 13}) or be restrained; on failure, they're petrified after the next failed save.
Venomous: Bite or sting attacks deliver venom — CON save (DC {1d4 + 12}) or take {2d8} poison damage and be poisoned for 1 minute.
Two Heads: Advantage on WIS (Perception) checks and on saving throws against being blinded, charmed, deafened, frightened, stunned, or knocked unconscious.
Regeneration: Regains {2d6 + 3} HP at the start of its turn unless it took acid or fire damage last round.
Spider Climb: Can climb difficult surfaces without ability checks.
Darting Attack: Can move up to 20 ft before or after any melee attack without provoking opportunity attacks.
Composite Physiology: {1d3} of the following attack types are available: claw, bite, gore, sting, constrict — each usable once per turn.
Threatening Presence: Hostile creatures entering within 30 ft for the first time on their turn must succeed on WIS saves (DC {1d4 + 12}) or be frightened.

// ----------------------------------------------------------------
// Actions by type
// ----------------------------------------------------------------

Table: action_Undead
Claw: Melee attack +{1d4 + 3} to hit, reach 5 ft. Hit: {1d6 + 2} slashing damage.
Life Drain: Melee attack +{1d4 + 4} to hit. Hit: {2d6 + 3} necrotic damage; target's HP maximum reduced by amount drained.
Paralyzing Touch: Melee attack; target must make CON save (DC {1d4 + 12}) or be paralyzed until end of next turn.
Shadow Step: Teleports from one shadow to another within 60 ft as a bonus action.
Bone Volley: Ranged attack, range 30/60 ft, +{1d4 + 3} to hit. Hit: {2d4 + 2} piercing damage.
Raise Dead (Recharge 5–6): Raises one corpse within 60 ft as a zombie under its control.
Wail of the Damned (Recharge 5–6): Banshee-like shriek; creatures within 30 ft make CON save (DC {1d4 + 14}) or drop to 0 HP; on success, take {3d8 + 4} psychic damage.
Draining Gaze: One creature within 60 ft makes CON save (DC {1d4 + 13}) or loses {1d10 + 2} HP maximum (restored after long rest).
Necrotic Burst (Recharge 5–6): Explodes in necrotic energy — 15 ft radius, DEX save (DC {1d4 + 12}), {4d8} necrotic damage (half on save).
Corrupting Touch: Melee attack +{1d4 + 5} to hit. Hit: {1d8 + 2} necrotic damage; target makes CON save or gains a level of exhaustion.

Table: action_Beast
Bite: Melee attack +{1d4 + 4} to hit, reach 5 ft. Hit: {2d6 + 3} piercing damage.
Claw: Melee attack +{1d4 + 3} to hit, reach 5 ft. Hit: {1d8 + 2} slashing damage.
Tail Swipe: Melee attack, all creatures in 10 ft arc must make DEX save (DC {1d4 + 11}) or take {2d6} bludgeoning damage.
Venomous Sting: Hit deals {1d6} poison damage; target makes CON save or is poisoned for 1 minute.
Roar (Recharge 6): All creatures within 30 ft must make WIS save (DC {1d4 + 12}) or be frightened.
Wing Attack: Each creature within 10 ft must make DEX save (DC {1d4 + 11}) or take {2d6} bludgeoning damage and be knocked prone.
Pounce: Moves up to its speed, then makes a bite attack; if it hits, the target must succeed on a STR save (DC {1d4 + 12}) or be knocked prone.
Constrict: Grapples target (escape DC {1d4 + 13}); while grappled, target takes {2d6 + 3} bludgeoning damage at start of each of the beast's turns.
Web (Recharge 5–6): Range 30/60 ft; target makes DEX save (DC {1d4 + 11}) or is restrained until it breaks free (STR DC {1d4 + 12}).
Gore: Melee attack +{1d4 + 5} to hit. Hit: {2d8 + 4} piercing damage; target makes STR save (DC {1d4 + 13}) or is pushed 10 ft.

Table: action_Humanoid
Longsword: Melee attack +{1d4 + 4} to hit. Hit: {1d8 + 3} slashing damage.
Shortbow: Ranged attack, range 80/320 ft, +{1d4 + 3} to hit. Hit: {1d6 + 2} piercing damage.
Shield Bash: Melee attack +{1d4 + 3} to hit. Hit: {1d4 + 2} bludgeoning damage; target makes STR save (DC {1d4 + 11}) or is knocked prone.
Rally: Grants {1d8} temporary HP to one ally within 30 ft.
Feint: Uses bonus action to grant advantage on next attack this turn.
Commander's Strike: A willing ally within 30 ft makes one melee attack as a reaction.
Poisoned Blade: Melee attack +{1d4 + 4} to hit. Hit: {1d6 + 3} piercing damage plus {2d6} poison damage; CON save (DC {1d4 + 12}) or poisoned for 1 minute.
Barbed Net (Recharge 5–6): Range 15 ft; target makes DEX save (DC {1d4 + 12}) or is restrained and takes {1d6} piercing damage whenever it tries to escape.
Dual Strike: Makes two light weapon attacks in a single action (+{1d4 + 3} each, {1d6 + 2} damage each).
Incite Violence: Uses action to force one ally it can see to make an attack against a target of its choice (WIS save DC {1d4 + 12} to resist).

Table: action_Fiend
Longsword: Melee attack +{1d4 + 5} to hit. Hit: {1d8 + 4} slashing + {1d6} fire damage.
Tail: Melee attack +{1d4 + 5} to hit. Hit: {2d8 + 4} bludgeoning damage; target makes CON save or is stunned until end of next turn.
Hellfire Ray: Ranged spell, range 120 ft. Hit: {3d8} fire damage.
Charm: Target makes WIS save (DC {1d4 + 13}) or is charmed for 1 hour.
Teleport: Magically teleports up to 120 ft to a visible unoccupied space.
Summon Minion (1/day): Summons {1d4} lesser fiends to serve until dismissed.
Flame Burst (Recharge 5–6): 20 ft radius centred on the fiend; DEX save (DC {1d4 + 14}); {5d8} fire damage (half on save).
Soul Rend: Melee attack +{1d4 + 6} to hit. Hit: {2d10 + 5} necrotic damage; if the target is reduced to 0 HP, its soul is trapped and cannot be resurrected without a Wish spell.
Binding Chains: Range 60 ft; target makes STR save (DC {1d4 + 14}) or is restrained and takes {1d8} necrotic damage per turn until freed.
Corruption: One creature the fiend can see within 60 ft must make CHA save (DC {1d4 + 13}); on failure, they are compelled to make an attack against their closest ally.

Table: action_Dragon
Bite: Melee attack +{1d6 + 7} to hit, reach 10 ft. Hit: {2d10 + 5} piercing damage + {1d10} elemental damage.
Claw: Melee attack +{1d6 + 7} to hit, reach 5 ft. Hit: {2d6 + 5} slashing damage.
Wing Attack: Each creature within 15 ft makes DEX save (DC {1d4 + 14}) or takes {2d6 + 5} damage and is knocked prone.
Tail: Melee attack +{1d6 + 7} to hit, reach 15 ft. Hit: {2d8 + 5} bludgeoning damage.
Breath Weapon (Recharge 5–6): 60 ft cone; DEX save (DC {1d4 + 17}); {8d6} elemental damage (half on save).
Frightful Presence: Each creature of choice within 120 ft makes WIS save (DC {1d4 + 14}) or is frightened for 1 minute.
Crush: Grapples one Large or smaller creature and slams it into the ground (STR save DC {1d4 + 16}); on failure, target is prone and takes {3d8 + 7} bludgeoning damage.
Elemental Nova (Recharge 5–6): Emanates elemental energy — 30 ft radius; DEX save (DC {1d4 + 17}); {6d10} elemental damage (half on save).
Swallow: Melee attack vs grappled target; if hit, the creature is swallowed and takes {2d6 + 5} acid damage per turn. The dragon regurgitates if it takes 30+ damage in one turn from inside.

Table: action_Construct
Slam: Melee attack +{1d4 + 6} to hit. Hit: {2d8 + 5} bludgeoning damage.
Rock Throw: Ranged attack, range 60/240 ft. Hit: {2d10 + 5} bludgeoning damage; target makes STR save or is knocked prone.
Siege Strike: Melee attack dealing {3d10 + 6} damage to structures and objects.
Overclock (Recharge 5–6): Gains an additional action on this turn.
Force Pulse: All creatures within 15 ft make STR save (DC {1d4 + 13}) or are pushed 10 ft and knocked prone.
Repair: Regains {2d8 + 4} HP (costs its action).
Chain Bind: Range 30 ft; launches chains at one target — DEX save (DC {1d4 + 14}) or restrained; STR save to break free (DC {1d4 + 14}).
Grinding Crush: Grappled target takes {3d6 + 6} bludgeoning damage at the start of each of the construct's turns.
Self-Destruct Protocol (Recharge 6): The construct explodes; all creatures within 20 ft take {6d8} force damage (DEX save DC {1d4 + 15} for half); the construct is reduced to 0 HP.

Table: action_Aberration
Tentacle: Melee attack +{1d4 + 5} to hit, reach 10 ft. Hit: {2d6 + 4} bludgeoning damage; target is grappled (escape DC {1d4 + 13}).
Mind Blast (Recharge 5–6): 60 ft cone; INT save (DC {1d4 + 15}); {5d8 + 4} psychic damage and stunned until end of next turn (half on save, not stunned).
Psychic Crush: Ranged spell, range 60 ft. Target makes INT save (DC {1d4 + 14}) or takes {3d8} psychic damage and is incapacitated.
Extract Brain: Melee attack vs grappled target. On hit, target takes {6d6} piercing damage; if reduced to 0, brain is extracted.
Telekinetic Throw: One creature or object within 60 ft makes STR save (DC {1d4 + 13}) or is hurled 30 ft and takes {2d6} damage.
Create Thrall: Touches an incapacitated humanoid; target is charmed indefinitely.
Reality Fracture (Recharge 5–6): 30 ft radius around the aberration; all creatures make INT save (DC {1d4 + 15}) or believe themselves to be in a different location (disadvantage on all attacks until end of next turn).
Drain Identity: One creature within 30 ft makes CHA save (DC {1d4 + 14}) or loses all memory of the last {1d4} hours and gains a false memory implanted by the aberration.
Spatial Grasp: Ranged attack; all creatures in a 30 ft cone make STR saves (DC {1d4 + 13}) or are pulled 30 ft toward the aberration.

Table: action_Fey
Shortsword: Melee attack +{1d4 + 4} to hit. Hit: {1d6 + 3} piercing damage.
Fey Charm: Target makes WIS save (DC {1d4 + 12}) or is charmed for 24 hours.
Blinding Dust: 10 ft radius; DEX save (DC {1d4 + 11}) or blinded until end of next turn.
Bewildering Glamour: Target makes WIS save (DC {1d4 + 12}) or uses its move to walk toward the fey.
Thorn Whip: Ranged attack, range 30 ft. Hit: {2d6 + 3} piercing damage; target is pulled 10 ft toward the fey.
Vanish: Turns invisible until it attacks or casts a spell.
Hypnotic Spiral: One creature within 60 ft makes WIS save (DC {1d4 + 13}) or is incapacitated and has speed 0 until end of next turn (mesmerised by swirling lights).
Glamoured Strike: Melee attack +{1d4 + 5} to hit. Hit: {1d8 + 4} damage; the target cannot distinguish whether the damage was lethal or illusory (disadvantage on death saves until a Medicine check DC 15 is made on them).
Mass Charm (Recharge 5–6): All creatures within 30 ft make WIS saves (DC {1d4 + 14}); those who fail are charmed for 1 minute and regard the fey as their most trusted ally.

Table: action_Giant
Greatclub: Melee attack +{1d4 + 7} to hit, reach 10 ft. Hit: {3d8 + 6} bludgeoning damage.
Rock: Ranged attack, range 60/240 ft. Hit: {3d10 + 6} bludgeoning damage.
Stomp: Melee attack vs prone target, +{1d4 + 7} to hit. Hit: {4d8 + 6} bludgeoning damage.
Sweeping Blow: All creatures in a 10 ft arc make DEX save (DC {1d4 + 14}) or take {2d10 + 6} bludgeoning damage and are knocked prone.
Hurl Boulder (Recharge 5–6): Throws a boulder up to 60 ft; creatures in a 10 ft radius make DEX save (DC {1d4 + 13}) or take {4d10} bludgeoning damage.
War Cry: Allies within 30 ft gain advantage on attack rolls until end of next turn.
Thunderclap (Recharge 5–6): Claps hands together, sending shockwave in 30 ft cone; DEX save (DC {1d4 + 14}), {5d8} thunder damage (half on save); those who fail are also deafened.
Grab and Smash: Grapples one creature (STR contest); next turn, slams the creature into the ground for {4d10 + 8} bludgeoning damage (no attack roll needed).
Avalanche Charge: Moves in a straight line up to 30 ft; all creatures in its path make DEX saves (DC {1d4 + 14}) or take {2d8 + 6} bludgeoning damage and are knocked prone.

Table: action_Ooze
Pseudopod: Melee attack +{1d4 + 4} to hit. Hit: {2d6 + 3} acid damage + {1d6} bludgeoning damage.
Engulf: Moves up to its speed; grappled creatures must make DEX save (DC {1d4 + 12}) or be engulfed (blinded, restrained, takes {2d6} acid damage per turn).
Acid Spray (Recharge 5–6): 15 ft cone; DEX save (DC {1d4 + 12}); {4d6} acid damage (half on save).
Corrode: Non-magical metal items on engulfed creature take a permanent –1 to AC/damage.
Split: Triggered reaction when takes lightning or slashing damage; two oozes appear.
Digest: Engulfed creature takes automatic {2d6} acid damage at start of each of the ooze's turns.
Acid Lash: Range 20 ft; target makes DEX save (DC {1d4 + 12}) or takes {3d8} acid damage and is blinded until end of next turn (acid splashes onto face).
Absorption: Melee attack; if it hits a creature wearing non-magical armour, the armour's AC bonus is reduced by 1 permanently.
Splitting Surge (Recharge 6): The ooze splits into {1d3 + 1} smaller oozes simultaneously (each has half the original's HP and damage dice).

