// Bonus actions / reactions by type
// ----------------------------------------------------------------

Table: bonus_Undead
Bonus Action — Shadow Meld: Moves through shadow to any location in dim light or darkness within 30 ft (doesn't provoke opportunity attacks).
Reaction — Deathless Surge: When reduced to 0 HP, immediately uses Undead Fortitude before losing consciousness.
Bonus Action — Soul Siphon: Drains {1d6} HP from a creature it has grappled.

Table: bonus_Beast
Bonus Action — Savage Lunge: After reducing a creature to 0 HP, moves up to half its speed and makes one melee attack.
Reaction — Feral Dodge: When targeted by a melee attack, imposes disadvantage on the roll (instinctive reflexes).
Bonus Action — Gnaw: Makes a secondary bite attack (+{1d4 + 2}, {1d4 + 1} damage) against a grappled creature.

Table: bonus_Humanoid
Bonus Action — Off-Hand Attack: Makes one light weapon attack with its bonus action.
Reaction — Parry: Adds {1d4 + 2} to its AC against one melee attack that would hit it (must see attacker).
Bonus Action — Shout Orders: One ally within 30 ft can make one melee attack as a reaction.

Table: bonus_Fiend
Bonus Action — Infernal Dash: Moves up to 60 ft without provoking opportunity attacks (fire trail ignites in its wake for 1 turn).
Reaction — Hellish Rebuke: When damaged by a melee attack, the attacker takes {2d10} fire damage (no save).
Bonus Action — Soul Exchange: Trades positions with a creature it has charmed (teleports both).

Table: bonus_Dragon
Bonus Action — Claw Rake: Makes one claw attack as a bonus action against a creature it has bitten this turn.
Reaction — Wing Buffet: When a creature enters melee range, the dragon knocks it back 10 ft (STR save DC {1d4 + 15}).
Legendary Action — Tail Sweep (costs 1): Makes a tail attack as a legendary action.

Table: bonus_Construct
Bonus Action — Overclock Step: Moves up to its full speed as a bonus action (can only do this once per turn).
Reaction — Absorb Impact: When hit by a weapon attack, reduces damage taken by {1d6 + 2} (thick plating absorbs force).
Bonus Action — Locking Grip: Tightens its grapple; grappled creature has disadvantage on its next escape attempt.

Table: bonus_Aberration
Bonus Action — Phase Blink: Partially phases into the Ethereal Plane until start of next turn; melee attacks against it have disadvantage.
Reaction — Mind Spike: When a creature within 60 ft casts a spell, the aberration can attempt to interrupt it (target makes INT save DC {1d4 + 13} or the spell fails).
Bonus Action — Psychic Leech: Drains {1d8} INT from a charmed creature (restored after long rest).

Table: bonus_Fey
Bonus Action — Fey Step: Teleports up to 30 ft to a visible unoccupied space.
Reaction — Mirror Image: When targeted by an attack, creates one illusory duplicate (25% chance the attack hits the duplicate instead).
Bonus Action — Beguiling Glance: One creature within 30 ft makes WIS save (DC {1d4 + 11}) or is distracted (disadvantage on its next attack before end of its next turn).

Table: bonus_Giant
Bonus Action — Intimidating Roar: All creatures within 30 ft make WIS save (DC {1d4 + 12}) or are frightened until end of their next turn.
Reaction — Catch: When a thrown weapon or rock misses it, the giant can catch the projectile and immediately hurl it at another target (same attack roll).
Bonus Action — Kick: Makes a kick attack (+{1d4 + 6} to hit; {1d10 + 5} bludgeoning damage) against one creature within 5 ft.

Table: bonus_Ooze
Bonus Action — Surge: Flows 20 ft toward the nearest living creature without provoking opportunity attacks.
Reaction — Engulf Response: When a creature tries to escape the ooze's grapple, the ooze immediately makes a pseudopod attack against it.
Bonus Action — Slick Trail: Leaves a patch of acid in its space (difficult terrain, {1d4} acid damage to enter) until the start of its next turn.

Table: bonus_Plant
Bonus Action — Vine Whip: Makes a free vine lash attack against a creature that has just moved adjacent to it.
Reaction — Thorned Recoil: When hit by a melee attack, attacker takes {1d6} piercing damage from thorns.
Bonus Action — Rapid Root: Plants roots into the ground; until it moves, its AC increases by 2 and it has advantage on STR saves.

Table: bonus_Monstrosity
Bonus Action — Rend: Makes one claw attack against a creature it has bitten this turn.
Reaction — Ferocious Counter: When hit by a melee attack, makes one melee attack of opportunity against the attacker.
Bonus Action — Repositioning Leap: Leaps up to 20 ft to any unoccupied space without provoking opportunity attacks.

// ----------------------------------------------------------------
// Lairs
// ----------------------------------------------------------------

Table: lair
a network of [|dark|flooded|crumbling|suffocating|reeking|lightning-scarred] caverns beneath the hills
the ruins of a [|castle|temple|watchtower|keep|villa|shipwreck] long abandoned
a fetid [|swamp|bog|marsh|mire|delta|mangrove] on the edge of civilised lands
a [|dense|enchanted|cursed|haunted|silent|fog-choked] forest no map dares name
the [|burnt|collapsed|overgrown|desecrated|frozen|half-flooded] remains of a village
a [|sunken|ice-encrusted|poisoned|blighted|windswept|ash-covered] valley shunned by all
deep within the [|mountains|glacier|desert|underground sea|volcanic tunnels|tidal caves]
the top floor of a [|blackened|cracked|leaning|half-sunk|lightning-struck|toppled] tower
a vast ossuary beneath a forgotten [|battlefield|monastery|noble estate|city]
a [|half-submerged|tide-locked|reef-tangled] sea cave accessible only at low tide
the centre of a dead forest where nothing has grown in [|decades|centuries|living memory]
a nest built from [|bones|shipwreck timber|stolen armour|petrified wood|crushed wagons]

// ----------------------------------------------------------------
// Behaviour
// ----------------------------------------------------------------

Table: behaviour
Territorial — attacks anything that enters its lair without provocation.
Cunning — studies intruders from a distance before striking.
Pack Leader — never encountered alone; {1d4 + 1} lesser minions follow it.
Ancient — wise and patient; may parley before resorting to violence.
Frenzied — attacks the nearest creature indiscriminately; pain enrages it.
Collector — hoards [|gold|magic items|bones|books|trinkets|weapons|teeth] and guards them jealously.
Nocturnal — inactive during daylight; terrifying at night.
Migratory — roams a vast territory; its lair shifts with the seasons.
Charmer — uses guile and illusion to avoid combat until the moment is right.
Corrupted — once noble, now twisted by [|dark magic|an ancient curse|a demon's pact|plague|exposure to wild magic].
Sentinel — guards a specific location or object; ignores all else unless threatened.
Wounded — injured by a prior encounter; more dangerous and less predictable for it.
Opportunistic — follows other predators to steal kills; retreats if outmatched.
Ritual-bound — performs the same behaviour at the same time daily; disrupting it causes a berserk rage.
Intelligent — uses tactics, flanking, and terrain; targets spellcasters and healers first.

